subject: re: server is rejecting mail from single domain
emailtext: james d. parra wrote  james d. parra wrote   hello   we have  client who just this month is getting  following error when  sending mail  us   the following recipients could not be reached   oyopvgiourdomain.com  2/8/2008 417 pm  there was  smtp communication problem with  recipients  email server. please contact your system administrator.    helo command  rejected need fullyqualified hostname     my postfix log says  following   feb 8 122104 postserver postfix/smtpd22189 warning 64.22.240.195  address not listed  hostname ns.ky3.com  feb 8 122105 postserver postfix/smtpd22189 noqueue reject rcpt   from   unknown64.22.240.195 504  helo command rejected need  fullyqualified hostname from      protoesmtp helo    what can i add   main.cf  allow this ip address  domain access?     tell  client  fix his helo name. spamserver is more than non  fqdn. its  provocation   if you prefer  surrender then remove rejectnonfqdnhostname   rejectnonfqdnhelohostname.     i can suggest that  him  this is  client so i can only ask. from   clients vantage point our server is  only one rejecting his mail so i  need  tread politely.  of course you need  find  right words... be helpful  firm. tell them  you will whitelist them so youre very open   you dont want anyone else  be whitelisted. so they must own  ip  they must take responsibility  all mail coming out  that ip  they may have delivery issues elsewhere. they may not realize it  some sites may be discarding their mail. and if that didnt happen yet chances are this will happen   future. many people are getting sick  supporting zombies because  broken sites. in short their system is not configured according   standards   helo name must be  fqdn hostname   ip literal  their system must have  correct reverse dns ipnameip must result   original ip.  concerning removing rejectnonfqdnhostname   rejectnonfqdnhelohostname is not something i want  do. if this  werent  client  ours i wouldnt worry too much about it  it is  i  must. is there  way could add  exception   main.cf  this domain   ip address?  it would have been easier if you showed your config. you need  put  checkclientaccess that returns ok  you must not put this   wrong place. here is  acceptable example smtpdrecipientrestrictions  ... rejectunauthdestination rejectnonfqdnsender rejectnonfqdnrecipient ... rejectinvalidhostname checkclientaccess cidr/etc/postfix/brokenclient rejectnonfqdnhostname ...  brokenclient 10.1.2.3/32 ok in short you should move your rejectnonfqdnhostname down enough  be able  add  brokenclient check before it without affecting other checks.  less appealing alternative is  make your rejectnonfqdnhostname  result   checkclientaccess  10.1.2.3/32 dunno 0.0.0.0/0 rejectnonfqdnhostname  this will only add complexity.

subject: re: [sm-users] autorespond plugin
emailtext: on 2/8/08 kenmiles wrote   i am using squirrelmail 1.4.13 with dovecote  postfix  ubuntu 6.10.  is there  way  have  autorespond plugin send  vacation message every  time  email is received from  same email address instead  just   first time  message is sent. thats not  question   plugin. the plugin merely sets  responder /off  with  message. your mail delivery system does  actual autoresponding. you need  know how  configure your autoresponse system. if you dont know how  do that read up  your mail system  ask   right forum. also note that local user autoresponder  mail forwarder will also work  you   answer  your question will still be  same.

emailtext: jonathan dill wrote  james d. parra wrote  i can suggest that  him  this is  client so i can only ask.  from   clients vantage point our server is  only one rejecting his mail  so i  need  tread politely.   concerning removing rejectnonfqdnhostname   rejectnonfqdnhelohostname is not something i want  do. if this  werent  client  ours i wouldnt worry too much about it  it is   i  must. is there  way could add  exception   main.cf  this  domain   ip address?    if he sent email  me my server would also reject it then you would  not be alone. but seriously i wonder if setting up /etc/nsswitch.conf   check files first  adding  entry  /etc/hosts would fix it e.g.   64.22.240.195 ns.ky3.com   i am not sure how postfix verifies fqdn if it uses  os resolver  stack  some other method. it is not  client hostname that is rejected its  helo name that  client itself determines  announces itself   receiving server. this is especially stupid since you have  configure  helo  your own system. so you can only kick  admin   server with  nonfqdnhelo  whitelist  client.  sandy list replies only please please address pms  newsreply2  japantest . homelinux . com

emailtext: now i get it i thought that postfix was complaining because host lookup   fqdn does not match  ip. but  be honest it looks  me like someone has owned their server  having  bit  fun because  server is literally announcing itself as spamserver   helo instead   fqdn  telnet 64.22.240.195 25 trying 64.22.240.195... connected  64.22.240.195. escape character is . 220 spamserver microsoft esmtp mail service version 6.0.3790.1830 ready at fri 8 feb 2008 165539 0800 sandy drobic wrote  jonathan dill wrote  james d. parra wrote  i can suggest that  him  this is  client so i can only ask.  from   clients vantage point our server is  only one rejecting his  mail so i  need  tread politely.   concerning removing rejectnonfqdnhostname   rejectnonfqdnhelohostname is not something i want  do. if this  werent  client  ours i wouldnt worry too much about it  it  is  i  must. is there  way could add  exception   main.cf  this  domain   ip address?    if he sent email  me my server would also reject it then you  would not be alone. but seriously i wonder if setting up  /etc/nsswitch.conf  check files first  adding  entry   /etc/hosts would fix it e.g.   64.22.240.195 ns.ky3.com   i am not sure how postfix verifies fqdn if it uses  os resolver  stack  some other method.   it is not  client hostname that is rejected its  helo name  that  client itself determines  announces itself   receiving  server.   this is especially stupid since you have  configure  helo  your  own system.   so you can only kick  admin   server with  nonfqdnhelo   whitelist  client.

subject: [uai] cfp: constraint solving & programming at 20th annual acm symposium on applied computing
emailtext: with apologies  multiple copies call for papers track  constraint solving  programming part   20th annual acm symposium  applied computing santa fe new mexico march 13 17 2005 http//www.sci.unich.it/7ebista/organizing/constraintsac2005/  overview constraints have emerged as  basis   representational  computational paradigm that draws from many disciplines  can be brought  bear  many problem domains.  scope the track is concerned with all aspects  computing with constraints including algorithms applications environments languages models  systems. contributions are welcome from any discipline concerned with constraints including artificial intelligence combinatorial algorithms computational logic concurrent computation databases discrete mathematics operations research programming languages  symbolic computation. we also solicit papers from any domain employing constraints including computational linguistics configuration decision support design diagnosis graphics hardware verification molecular biology planning qualitative reasoning realtime systems resource allocation robotics scheduling software engineering temporal reasoning vision visualization  user interfaces. papers that bridge disciplines  combine theory  practice  discuss novel reasoning methods are especially welcome. a special attention is focused around  use  constraint technologies   networking wireless  internet fields.  submissions we would like  invite authors  submit papers  research  constraint solving  programming with particular emphasis  assessing  current state   art  identifying future directions. preliminary guidelines submissions should be properly anonymized  facilitate blind reviewing papers being submitted should not list  authors affiliations  addresses   first page  authors are also encouraged  take care throughout  entire document  minimise references that may reveal  identity   authors  institution. the body  each paper should not exceed 4000 words. papers failing  comply with length limitations risk immediate rejection. at least three reviewers will be assigned  each submission   track. accepted papers are published by acm  both printed form  cdrom they are also available   web through  acm digital library. once accepted papers must fit within five 5 two column pages please check  author kit   main sac website  format is usually  format used   acm templates with  option at additional expense  add three 3 more pages. a second set  selected papers which did not get accepted as full papers will be accepted as posters  will be published as extended 2page abstracts   symposium proceedings. authors  accepted papers must be prepared  sign  copyright statement  must pay  registration fee  guarantee that their paper will be presented at  conference. paper submissions should be sent as  attached pdf file  ayngnxt.ktvtegfzlaiit.cnr.it the body   email should include  title   paper  authors names  affiliations   address including email telephone  fax  which correspondence should be sent. the subject   email should be sac2005 constraint track submission we strongly suggest  use  submission  available camera ready templates  adhere   5 page limitation. registration is required  paper  poster inclusion   conference proceedings   event attendance.  important dates the proposed schedule  important dates   track is as follows paper submission deadline august 31 2004 notification  acceptance october 18 2004 cameraready version deadline november 2 2004 track dates march 1317 2005  organisation organising committee   stefano subject: re: sa-learn --ham ground rules
emailtext: on friday 08 february 2008 karsten brckelmann wrote on fri 20080208 at 0149 0500 gene heskett wrote  the salearn spam can process  message  5  10 seconds  so so if  ive dropped 20 doofus mails   spam directory  fire it off i have  it done  kmail is back among  living  23 minutes.  this seems way too high. if there have been only 20 messages total  that folder salearn should have processed these   few seconds  less.   but feeding it  ham directory with about 7k messages  it turned  salearn into  100 cpu hog ...  what did you expect? based  your numbers above processing that folder would have taken 1020 hours...   incrementing  message processed number only  about every 3  5 minutes. i couldnt kill it it kept coming back  i  must have fed it  kill 9 50 times.  hmm. kmail doesnt start one process per mail by any chance?   so what is  maximum number  files   directory that one can feed   salearn ham  expect it  achieve normal speed?  dunno if there are limitations  however your 7k messages should be perfectly fine. just ran  test   6k messages mbox file  there was no noticeable difference   30 messages test.   the command that kmail issues  it is  salearn ham /root/mail/foldername/cur  youre not using root as your ordinary user account do you ?   guenther in fact i do  i have myself somewhat   sandbox as all  mail handling stuff except kmail runs as  unprivileged user  kmail pulls incoming from that mailbox  /var. ive been doing that  about 23  years started it back at fc2. and running as root since rh5.1. yeah im  unrepentant old fart.  cheers gene there are four boxes  be used  defense  liberty soap ballot jury  ammo. please use  that order. ed howdershelt author cpu needs recalibration

subject: [lwv-healthcare] millions with chronic illness go untreated - ny times
emailtext: http//www.nytimes.com/ http//www.nytimes.com/ adx/bin/adxclick.html?typegoto&pagewww.nytimes.com/printerfriendly&posposition1&sn2336c557e/4f3dd5d2&sn1e0a6eda9/40ceca0d&ca mpfoxsearch2008emailtools810906dnyt5&adbiggie88x318k.gif&gotohttp//my foxsearchlight.com/profile/waynebarrow  august 5 2008 millions with chronic disease get little  no treatment by reed abelson http//topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/people//reedabelson/index.html?inlinenytper millions  americans with chronic disease like diabetes http//health.nytimes.com/health/guides/disease/diabetes/overview.html?inlinenytclassifier  high blood pressure http//health.nytimes.com/health/guides/disease/hypertension/overview.html?inlinenytclassifier are not getting adequate treatment because they are among  nations growing ranks  uninsured. that is  central finding   new study  be published tuesday   medical journal annals  internal medicine. the study  first detailed look at  health   uninsured estimates that about one  every three workingage adults without insurance   united states has received  diagnosis   chronic illness. many  these people are forgoing doctors visits  relying  emergency rooms  their medical care  study said. the report based   analysis  government health surveys  adults ages 18  64 years old estimated that about 11 million   36 million people without insurance  2004   latest year   study  had received  chroniccondition diagnosis. these are people who with modern therapies can be kept out  trouble said dr. andrew p. wilper  studys lead author. therapies  someone with diabetes  hypertension are routine  widely available if you have insurance said dr. wilper  medical instructor at  university  washington http//topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/organizations/u/universit yofwashington/index.html?inlinenytorg  seattle. the most recent government estimate   number  people  this country without health insurance http//topics.nytimes.com/top/news/health/diseasesconditionsandhealthtopics/healthinsuranceandmanagedcare/index.html?inlineny tclassifier is 47 million which means that if  proportions found   study have remained constant there might be nearly 16 million people  this country with  chronic condition  no insurance  pay  medical care. nearly  quarter   uninsured with  chronic illness who were surveyed said they had not visited  health professional within  last year. about 7 percent said they typically went   hospital emergency room  care. a lot  people are suffering from  lack  health insurance said dr. steffie woolhandler another   studys authors who is  physician  associate professor  medicine at harvard. people with high blood pressure  example are at risk  catastrophic medical events like  stroke if they are not getting  drugs they need  having  doctor monitor their disease said karen davis  president   commonwealth fund. the fund  foundation  new york that specializes  health care research has done its own research into  lack  adequate medical care among  uninsured. the study being published tuesday may have underestimated exactly how many people who are uninsured have  chronic illness because it includes only those who have already received such  diagnosis  authors said. individuals who have not had their conditions diagnosed because they are not seeing  doctor  nurse are not included. the studys authors say that their findings cast doubt   common assumption that many   uninsured tend  be young  healthy requiring little   way  medical care. because so many actually have chronic conditions that may be expensive  treat  cost  covering  uninsured is often underestimated said dr. woolhandler who advocates  nationalized system  health care. in massachusetts she said  states effort  overhaul its health insurance system  cover more residents is costing much more than expected  has not led  universal coverage because policy makers assumed that more people would be healthy. the state experiments have all failed because  cost she said. the study describes harsh consequences  neglecting easily treatable diseases  so many people. for some   11.4 million uninsured americans with serious chronic conditions access  care seems  be unobtainable many may face early disability  death as  result  studys authors said. looking   car thats sporty subject: [uai] cp 2004 call for participation
emailtext: sorry this is going out late  i was out  town... bda dear colleague as cochairs  cp 2004  be held  toronto september 27  october 1 2004 we would like extend  invitation  you  participate   conference. important date today august 19 2004 deadline  obtain  room at conference hotel at  conference rate. the conference rate is 169 canadian dollars 128 us dollars 107 euros. after  cutoff date  room rate is expected  be much higher at 269. highlights   conference include  a strong technical program featuring highly reviewed technical papers  distinguished keynote speakers andreas podelski mpi germany bart selman cornell u. usa helmut simonis ic parc uk  jeanfrangois puget ilog france  an outstanding workshop  tutorial program  a social program including  conference banquet  opening reception more details can be found   web at http//ai.uwaterloo.ca/cp2004/ hope  see you  toronto fahiem bacchus peter van beek cochairs cp 2004

subject: re: [opensuse] opensuse 11
emailtext: basil chupin wrote  james knott wrote   is there no way  add another user? i try  convince my friends   create  user account separate from  admin. it sounds like another  security bomb is about  go off.     i quote from  book i have   xp   quote   windows xp home edition bestows administrator rights  anyone who  logs into  computer giving full control  all system resources   this is not  satisfactory security model  business  power users.    unquote.   answer your question?   my question was about vista. my thinkpad came with xp home  i have both admin  user accounts  it. user accounts  xp home do not have admin rights. however most people never get past that first account which does have admin rights.  use openoffice.org

subject: re: [opensuse] 10.3 and powermanagement
emailtext: on thursday 07 february 2008 072352 am aaron kulkis wrote  john e. perry wrote   as i mentioned  yet another thread hp wants me  dump suse    restore  machine  its original xp pro configuration then theyll   work with me  find out if my hardware problems no sound either under   xp  suse bad readings from kde power switch dead can be fixed under   warranty.   for this reason  only this reason i pull  windows  drive  buy  different drive  put suse .   when  computer needs repair.. original drive with   windows installation goes back  solely  please   techs.  fwiw i had  hp dv6000 with hardware problems  when i made  support call i did tell them i was running linux though i resisted any suggestions  try windows  forced them  diagnose it anyways. when i got my ticket  send it   service i pulled  drive altogether  placed  sticky  it saying hdd removed  corporate policy reasons. they fixed my system  sent it back three days later. if you have  hardware problem dont bother including  drive. they can troubleshoot it without it  it keeps them from sending it back saying wont fix because you have linux  it. just my 2c... cheers kv

subject: re: sa-learn --ham ground rules
emailtext: from gene heskett sent friday 2008 february 08 1643  on friday 08 february 2008 karsten brckelmann wrote on fri 20080208 at 0149 0500 gene heskett wrote  the command that kmail issues  it is  salearn ham /root/mail/foldername/cur  youre not using root as your ordinary user account do you ?   guenther   in fact i do  i have myself somewhat   sandbox as all  mail  handling  stuff except kmail runs as  unprivileged user  kmail pulls incoming  from that mailbox  /var. ive been doing that  about 23  years  started it back at fc2. and running as root since rh5.1. yeah im   unrepentant old fart. gene how many times have i told you dont do that with linux? old fart  not you broke it. now you get  fix it. you declared you run all mail handling as  unprivileged user. then you try  run salearn as root  roots mailbox. there is rather  problem there if you think about it. sit  ruminate  few minutes. seriously  think. have you considered what you are doing  where at least one hyperobvious problem lies? if youre not banging your forehead  screaming doh by now here is  clue bat. if youve figured it out duck spamassassin will be using  bayes database collected as that unprivileged user. it cannot use one generated as root  placed  roots directory structure. the last i knew you were trying  use per user bayes. so salearn as root will build  file   place  unprivileged process cannot access and will likely leave  file with privileges that prevent access by that unprivileged user. thats issue one  you  fix. and if you dont fix your errant ways mamas gonna whup you good. what size machine are you trying  work ? how deep into your swap file are you when you run salearn?  joanne ashamed ive known you all these years gene. you shame me by not taking advice repeated virtually every time we communicate.

emailtext: http//issues.apache.org/spamassassin/showbug.cgi?id5667  additional comments from jqqal2mbit.com 20071003 0628  in reply  comment 1  in reply  comment 0   for providers who use our dnsbl service you must make sure  alert your   customers   fact that you are using our service   support pages    signup pages with  link  our website. your customers have  right  know   what methods you are using  filter their email.     this would be tricky  us...    duh. were talking about  rhsbl service not  dnsbl one. load is  issue yes  becoming less  one since we started getting some new mirrors. our usage information is outdated  we recommend that groups/companies be forthcoming with their their users   topic  how their mail is filtered  not  requirement anymore. ive made  note  fix  pages. for  record weve been doing uribl style lookups against  rhsbl with very much success  over 2 years now with no negative issues. id go so far  say that it works better as  uribl rhsbl then as  from domain checker. brie bruns founder & sr. systems admin the sosdg / ahbl  you are receiving this mail because  you are  assignee   bug  are watching  assignee.

subject: re: [opensuse] intel 3945 wireless problem opensuse 10.3
emailtext: on thu 20080207 at 1935 0800 kai ponte wrote  one problem down one  go.   i cant seem  connect  my  any other wifi network with my laptop.   i have  intel 3945 abg card  my laptop. it is loaded with  ipw3945d  regulatory daemon ipw3945kmpdefault ipwfirmware  iwl3945ucode   iwlifikmpdefault files  yast.   i have network setup  be user controlled using knetworkmanager. though  previously hidden i have my ssid open with no password.   i can see my network  cannot connect. the knetworkmanager progress bar gets   28 then quits.   i also tried this   few  my neighbors open wifi networks  i cant get   them either.    on  previous attempt  setup 10.3  this laptop i was intermittently able   get   wifi. 10.2 had no issues.   ive googled  not found much  help out.   ideas?   both myself   coworker had  same problem  our new dell latitude d630 laptops. fresh installs  10.3. we could see  access point  could not connect  majority   time. when we were able  connect signal strength   gnome network manager applet would be   low teens speed would never be above 24 mbs  overall performance would be extremely poor. after much troubleshoot i discovered that during installation both  ipw3945   iwl3945 kernel modules got installed. yast chose  ipw3945 module when setting up  wireless. from some   messages ive seen when googleing intel 3945 there seem  be some significant issues with  ipw3945 kernel driver. the fix is   yast select configure   wireless card. select  hardware tab then change  kernel module   module name drop down list from  ipw3945   iwl3945. save  settings  exit out  yast. reboot  laptop. if  iwl3945 kernel module is not   list install it first then reboot  change. according   chatter some   features   iwl3945 module are done yet. like illuminating  blue wifi light  displaying  connection speed   network manager. but other than those cosmetic issues it is reliable  works every time i boot. i have no trouble going between  office wireless  my home wireless  using any other wifi connection i have tried. give it shot  let us know how it works.

emailtext: hi brian thanks again   advice it is appreciated. i had come across u0394 code through  character map  i get  u0394 error invalid uxxxx sequence so when i execute your code i get    a  b  stbacat  paste u0394 b error invalid uxxxx sequence this is  both rgui at home  at work windows vista  r 2.6 at home windows xp  r 2.7 at work thanks again gabors suggestion worked. original message from prof brian ripley mailtoripleystats.ox.ac.uk sent tue 05/08/2008 744 pm to michael watson iahc cc henrique dallazuanna rhelprproject.org subject re r greek characters  plots on tue 5 aug 2008 michael watson iahc wrote  ok i am definitely struggling here.   the text i am trying  plot isnt  mathematical expression its   a ?stbacat ok so you want  greek character  not  greek symbol. as i said they are different different fonts different shapes aka glyphs.  this is biological notation   particular mutation. the a part is   tag identifying  graph   stbacat bit is  gene that is  mutated. both  tag  gene are set as variables   loop  only   delta remains  same.   as  text i am trying  plot isnt  mathematical expression i seem   be having trouble getting substitute  expression  do what i  want. as plotmath states a mathematical expression must obey   normal rules  syntax  any r expression i fear i may be barking up   wrong tree   thank you all  your help so far  can someone please help me once  more  tell me how i can get  capital delta symbol so i can use it   nonmathematical text  strings  plotting?   a b  stbacat paste u0394 b number from http//www.alanwood.net/unicode/greek.html . this should work   utf8 locale  also  windows   windows device    rgui console.   thanks once again   mick   original message  from prof brian ripley mailtoripleystats.ox.ac.uk  sent 05 august 2008 1240  to michael watson iahc  cc henrique dallazuanna rhelprproject.org  subject re r greek characters  plots   on tue 5 aug 2008 michael watson iahc wrote   excellent i even tried delta  not delta....   ?plotmath says   alpha  omega uppercase greek symbols   how could that be made clearer?   note it carefully says greek symbols not character they are not   same thing.   now how do i go about pasting that with some text that i have  various other variables?   use substitute? e.g.   substituteexpressionfoodelta listfoo3   some people prefer bquote  that is just  wrapper  substitute   r.    original message  from henrique dallazuanna mailtowwwhsdgmail.com  sent 05 august 2008 1217  to michael watson iahc  cc rhelprproject.org  subject re r greek characters  plots   try   expressiondelta   on tue aug 5 2008 at 814 am michael watson iahc  wrote  hi   i am running  r script that creates 100s  graphs  i need  use   greek capital letter delta   mtext function.   i got as far as expressiondelta  this gives me  lowercase  version.   can anyone help? subject: re: [opensuse] ssh: connection reset by peer
emailtext: user spin wrote  hello  i have  problem with ssh.  usually i work connected  several machines from  pc with opensuse  10.2. but when i do  some from my laptop  connection is closed  after some time  inactivity.  the message i get   terminal is  read from remote host xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx connection reset by peer  connection  xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx closed.   how can i tell  my laptop dont close connection   thank you. there is  setting somewhere i dont know where  it is about 300 secs  5 mins.  inactivity. if im going away   moment  two just start tailf /var/log/mail if  mail server  tailf /var/log/messages if you have some syslog activity  that will hold  connection until you get back another more proper way  do it is  use screen  detach  session leave it running  then reattach when necessary. note this doesnt save  lot  keystrokes  if you have  process   remote system you need  leave running either screen  backgrounding  process makes  most sense. see man screen basically just type screen  any terminal then ctrl h  choose detach  ctrl d.  david c. rankin j.d. p.e. rankin law firm pllc 510 ochiltree street nacogdoches texas 75961 telephone 936 7159333 facsimile 936 7159339 www.rankinlawfirm.com

filespeccatdir will put  path back together. the / trick only works if  string is  directory name with unix style directory delimiters  no directory delimiters. it is  force vmsify  treat  input specification as unix. there is  vmsfilespecunixpath  do  appending   /   specification which will do  vmsfilespecvmsify if needed. however it is not  good idea  call vmsify   pathname returned by unixify  it is not  good idea  call unixify   pathname returned by vmsify. because   nature   conversion not all file specifications can make  round trip. i think that directory specifications can safely make  round trip  not ones containing filenames. john ho0ebgqsl.net personal opinion only

contenttype text/plain charsetiso88591 hi all. here are test patches which should be  interest  this whove been having problems with  i/o speed. im providing patches  2.6.23.15  2.6.24.1. the whole lowlevel i/o code has had quite  rework. in /sys/power/tuxonice/blockio  only remaining entry is targetoutstandingio which can be used  say how much memory youd like  have made available  i/o. if more is available it will be used too. theres one new entry   /sys/power/tuxonice directory  noflusherthread. this entry is only useful if youve got multiple cpus/cores  then only if nomultithreadedio is 0 ie multithreaded i/o is enabled. what ive done is this by default we now dedicate one thread  cpu 0 one  just submitting i/o. all other threads spend their time compressing pages  filling pages with  compressed data  associated metadata then queueing filled pages   submission thread  handle. if theres only one thread  noflusherthread is used we go back   old behaviour  threads compress fill pages  submit them. so... options  multicore users 1 single threaded operation procsetting nomultithreadedio 1 2 multithreaded flusher thread default procsetting nomultithreadedio 0 procsetting noflusherthread 0 3 multithreaded no flusher thread procsetting nomultithreadedio 0 procsetting noflusherthread 1 if you give  patches  try would you please let me know how these different options subject: strange headers on mail from sa users list
emailtext: a weird thing has started within  last couple  days. it is only affecting mail received from  sa users mail list  only  mail received from paul douglas franklin  yakima ugm the messages have  to header like this to wlbpaliggfadgregorie.org users can.gregorie.org vzsgregorie.org qegongregorie.org pegregorie.org bagregorie.org mgregorie.org nrdmgregorie.org qpbvcgregorie.org tutorial?gregorie.org nosgregorie.org pupgregorie.org egregorie.org ytrggregorie.org eutbagregorie.org zjlgregorie.org ive edited it slightly  i line wrapped it   group 81 replaces  character with  hex value  0x81. i had  change it because  its original form it was corrupting  header when i pasted it into this message. i think its not anything malicious  that its bitten mail sent by mr. franklin because  something unique   headers when his response reached  sa listserver. i think it may have something  do with  sa mailing list software. reasons  in  past ive noticed that mail ive sent has appeared   mailing list minus  first line   body. when i looked at what i sent  first line was present  correct  if i pick off  mailbox part  all addresses after  0x81 byte i get can you point me   good regex tutorial? the one i have found has which is  first line  mr. franklins message. in  message i received  body  this message starts from his second line given me  lot  good starting stuff  it doesnt mention  ? has anybody else seen this problem? id really like this  be fixed as its littering my mail archiving system with junk addresses. im unable  include  message as received  sorry. ive tried  its content is causing evolution  corrupt  outgoing headers. martin

subject: re: cpanplus::backend.pm module_tree requires case preserving file systems.
emailtext: on 03 oct 2007 at 0748 john e. malmberg wrote  i have not worked out  fix yet  it seems that  last test  that is failing  vms is because ods2 does not retain  case   filenames that are created.   the problem is  filename is being converted   module name   then looked up   modtree hash. thanks  this diagnosis..  this case  fix is actually simple instead  doing  lookup straight   module tree we search   pattern with qr/mod/i  it will find it that way  this means it needs  spend  few more cpu cycles getting  right answer   patch becomes easy  lib/cpanplus/internals/search.pm revision 2250  lib/cpanplus/internals/search.pm local  2957 29518  mod  join  filespecsplitdirmod return if seenmod  my modobj  selfmoduletreemod  return  my modobj  do   onvms  ? selfsearch  type  module  allow  qr/mod/i     selfmoduletreemod      seperate return  list context return with one    it is also true  return unless modobj push rv modobj  ive applied this patch   development version  cpanplus.  jos boumans how do i prove im not crazy  people who are?

subject: [uai] 2nd cfp: flairs 2005--special track on uncertain reasoning
emailtext: call  papers special track  uncertain reasoning the 18th international flairs conference flairs2005 in cooperation with the american association  artificial intelligence adams mark hotel clearwater beach fl may 1618 2005 http//janus.newcs.uwindsor.ca/danwu/flairs2005/indexflairs2005.htm http//ranger.uta.edu/flairs05/  the capability  reasoning with uncertain / incomplete information is  crucial feature both  human  machine intelligence. the special track  uncertain reasoning at  eighteenth international florida artificial intelligence research symposium flairs conference seeks  bring together researchers working  broad issues related  reasoning under uncertainty. this track was started  1996  has become  annual event at flairs. in 2003  track was merged with  special track  imprecise  indeterminate probabilities. papers  all aspects  uncertain reasoning  imprecise probabilities are solicited. topics  interest include  are not limited   uncertain reasoning  databases  uncertain reasoning formalisms calculi  methodologies  reasoning with probability possibility fuzzy logic belief functions argumentation rough sets  probability logics  modelling  reasoning using imprecise  indeterminate information  using  instance choquet capacities comparative orderings convex sets  measures  intervalvalued probabilities  exact approximate  qualitative uncertain reasoning  nonmonotonic reasoning  belief revision  multiagent uncertain reasoning  decision making  decisiontheoretic planning  markov decision process  temporal reasoning  uncertainty  construction  models from elicitation data mining  knowledge discovery  uncertain reasoning  information retrieval filtering fusion diagnosis prediction  situation assessment  practical applications  uncertain reasoning paper submission  publication  paper format  submission details are available at http//earth.cs.ccsu.edu/flairs/submission.html papers will be refereed  all accepted papers will appear   conference proceedings which will be published by aaai press. selected authors will be invited  submit extended versions  their papers   special issue   international journal  artificial intelligence tools ijait  be published  2006. in addition we will be arranging  special issue   international journal  approximate reasoning devoted  extended  revised papers selected from  special track  uncertain reasoning.   thanks once again   mick   original message  from prof brian ripley mailtoripleystats.ox.ac.uk  sent 05 august 2008 1240  to michael watson iahc  cc henrique dallazuanna rhelprproject.org  subject re r greek characters  plots   on tue 5 aug 2008 michael watson iahc wrote   excellent i even tried delta  not delta....   ?plotmath says   alpha  omega uppercase greek symbols   how could that be made clearer?   note it carefully says greek symbols not character they are not   same thing.   now how do i go about pasting that with some text that i have  various other variables?   use substitute? e.g.   substituteexpressionfoodelta listfoo3   some people prefer bquote  that is just  wrapper  substitute   r.    original message  from henrique dallazuanna mailtowwwhsdgmail.com  sent 05 august 2008 1217  to michael watson iahc  cc rhelprproject.org  subject re r greek characters  plots   try   expressiondelta   on tue aug 5 2008 at 814 am michael watson iahc  wrote  hi   i am running  r script that creates 100s  graphs  i need  use   greek capital letter delta   mtext function.   i got as far as expressiondelta  this gives me  lowercase  version.   can anyone help? subject: re: [python-dev] adventures with x64 vs7 and vs8 on windows
emailtext: at 114 pm 0000 5/29/07 kristjn valur jnsson wrote  original message   microsofts command line cannot cope with two pathnames that must be  quoted so if  command path itself must be quoted then no argument     command can be quoted. there are tricky hacks that can work around  this mindboggling stupidity  life is simpler if python itself  doesnt  use up  one quoted pathname. i dont know if microsoft has had   good  sense  fix this  vista which i probably will never use since   alternative exists  they didnt  xp.  do you have any references  this claim? in my command line  xp sp2 this works just fine  cprogram filesmicrosoft visual studio 8vccprogram filestextpad 4textpad.exe ctmpf .txt ctmpf b.txt  both  program   two file names are quoted  textpad.exe opens them both. i pounded my head against this issue when working   .bat file  few years back until i read  help  cmd  saw  quote logic  switched  vbscript. its still there  help cmd. i had once found references   same issue   run command  microsofts online help. perhaps it is fixed  sp2. if so just change it  dont worry about users with earlier versions  windows.   tonyn.  pythondev mailing list zvlllneumpython.org http//mail.python.org/mailman/listinfo/pythondev unsubscribe http//mail.python.org/mailman/options/pythondev/pythondev40tangomu.com

subject: re: [opensuse] how can i write man pages? linuxdoc/docbook anyone? report on manedit
emailtext: begin pgp signed message hash sha1 the thursday 20080207 at 1105 0500 joe zonker brockmeier wrote .   maybe someone will pick it up  run with  program since it doesnt seem    be actively developed anymore.   yes it is mantained  see changelog   oh oops. im happy im wrong there then.   good luck with it please let us know how it goes. here i go. im writing this notes as i go  ill post when i finish. 1 it is designed   older set  libraries. gtkwarning  failed  load module libgnomebreakpad.so libgnomebreakpad.so cannot open shared object file no such file  directory but it does exist  /usr/lib/gtk2.0/modules/libgnomebreakpad.so. i guess it is looking   older version. 2 it does not support utf8 it displays latin1  when i type  accented letter it displays two strange letters  so no utf. i had  start  xterm  latin1 langenus.iso88591 lcallenus.iso88591 /usr/bin/xterm bd blue &  from there i fire up manedit. this could be  worst problem  all because there is no way  edit  utf8 with manedit. do you know if current man pages are supposed  be utf  latin1? see later 3 it is  xml editor which it translates  troff when saving  it is not wysiwyg   that is what you said  your write up. id like it  have  toggle  show  formatted output  no. 4 it warns that if i enable syntax highlighting it may crash. so far it hasnt  who knows... 5 i can not even change  font size  letters get substituted by squares  i loose accents. i had  delete  configuration file  restore working defaults. it must be  byproduct  not supporting utf. ... i havent finished yet  i found  blocker. the program does it job fairly well   locale encoding turns out  be  problem. i asked  people   project  whom im translating their pages whether they wanted  pages  latin1  utf8   answer is neither  characters outside  ascii printable range must be encoded see  groffchar7  note that we use e rather than e. this is  problem too with manual pages   suse distro they either display well  latin 1   utf 8  not both. and using  encoding described  groffchar7 they display correctly  both. the blocker is that manedit does not support that encoding. i would have  write ole instead  ol which may be just  nuisance   coder  it is  big inconvenience   writer i can not spell check  file  my sight doesnt see ol  gibberish so i cant proofread  text. / i dont understand how nobody has created  good program  writing documentation man files by mere mortals not by coders. and i do understand now why some projects refuse altogether  create  man page  make do instead with html  pdf files  why man page translations are so obsolete as  be useless when they do exist. i have also discarded  some tried gmanedit gconglomerate gjots2 pandoc zoem... i dont know what i will do. /   cheers carlos e. r. begin pgp signature version gnupg v2.0.4svn0 gnu/linux id8dbqfhra1jttmyhg2nr9urarlyaj9obtm3271fnflrrug9b5vomrlmwcgjp7c 5p3ynzlo4t4mde0cj3h3dxm snzp end pgp signature

emailtext: as regards  network cards sound cards  other such equipment is  it possible  have direct access  vbox  does this cause problems  with  host system? no. the problem is that if you enable such access your vm virtual machine will no longer be isolated so  code will leak  it may destroy data  your host physical pc. this is very unsafe.  alexey eremenko technologov

emailtext: hi all could it be that during installation ipv6 is not enabled? at work aswell as at home ive my own installationserver / gwdgmirror. identical setup  at home i use  all my vhosts  v6 address. after  system is installed i can upgrade  add aditional repos without any problem with my ipv6 servers. however during  initial installation  installation source coming froman ipv6 address are not recognised. if i perform  dvdinstallation just before  first boot i saw that  module ipv6 is not loaded. i presume this could be  reason. any suggestions how i can load this module  grub before installation takes place so that i can add my own installationsources? hans

emailtext: bugs item 988095 was opened at 20040709 1000 message generated  change comment added made by zianchoy you can respond by visiting https//sourceforge.net/tracker/?funcdetail&atid498103&aid988095&groupid61702 please note that this message will contain  full copy   comment thread including  initial issue submission  this request not just  latest update. category outlook group 1.0.4 status open resolution none priority 5 private no submitted by mlarma mlarma assigned  mark hammond mhammond summary dep / nx causes outlook  crash initial comment when enabling  nx function underneath winxp with sp2 rc2 32 bit edition not 64 bit windows i was unable  start outlook with  spambayes plug. after disabling  only disabling nx remove /noexecute from boot.ini it worked. funny thing is that  owner   company i work  developed  bayesian spam filter as well  it had  same issue with  nx. not sure what  problem is   nx feature would be nice  turn . does anyone know if nx can be disabled at  application level so that  other processes were protected with nx? mark  comment by zian zianchoy date 20070604 0335 message logged in yes userid1059620 originator no the dep /nx issue is not restricted  athlon chips. i am using  intel core 2 duo processor. when dep is enabled via software   system dialog  windows xp mce probably also applies  windows vista outlook fails  load  plugin. the web page text needs  remove  processor limitation.  comment by jimmy retzlaff jretz date 20061207 2310 message logged in yes userid101588 originator no ive tried  few basic python programs packaged with py2exe 0.6.5  python 2.4 with hardware dep enabled  windows xp sp2   newer pentiumm with xd support   windows server 2003   athlon 64 with nx support. everything seems  work fine. i tried all  py2exes bundle options  couldnt get windows  complain. the python scripts i used  testing only do simple arithmetic  make use  easydialogs  windows which uses ctypes.  comment by tony meyer anadelonbrin date 20060205 0020 message logged in yes userid552329 does that mean you predict that any py2exe program would fail  run? if so im happy  put together  hello world program  attach it so people can verify that this is  case.  comment by mark hammond mhammond date 20060204 2306 message logged in yes userid14198 just noting that  pythonwin issue appears related   dde module  this is not used by spambayes. im therefore back  suspecting py2exe.  comment by tony meyer anadelonbrin date 20051205 0047 message logged in yes userid552329 a lot  people are hitting this these days so changing  summary   hope that people will notice this bug  not submit new ones its already   faq.  comment by mark hammond mhammond date 20050809 2231 message logged in yes userid14198 just had  report that pythonwin also fails with this turned . this makes it less likely  problem is simply py2exe.  comment by mark hammond mhammond date 20050722 1106 message logged in yes userid14198 another possibility is that py2exe is  culprit. it isnt obvious  me that is is  problem  it certainly is possible. it would be interesting  know if  source version  spambayes has  same problem. when i get back  aus i will try  reproduce this.  comment by paul quinn paulquinn date 20040720 0804 message logged in yes userid815032 this is  problem with nx protection...this is how i got it  work there are ways  disable nx at application level  through  ui... i control panel  system ii click   advanced tab iii under performance section click settings iv click   data execution prevention tab v click add  select  appication you want  disable nx  b registry... under hkeylocalmachinesoftwaremicrosoftwindows ntcurrentversionappcompatflagslayers there are equivalent hkeycurrentuser keys create  new string key its name being  full path   executable file you want  disable nx   value being disablenxshowui .youll notice that   ui only executable files can be added. this means that i had  select  outlook.exe file  get spambayes  work again. i tried adding  spambayesaddin.dll   python23.dll paths   registry as  workaround  this didnt work... also if you are using outlook 2003 you may need  reenable  plug by deleting its resilliency key  com add manager wont remember  reenable setting no matter how many times you try http//groups.google.co.uk/groups? hlen&lr&ieutf8&safeoff&selmuz24fjzyfeha.3984 40tk2msftngp10.phx.gbl fyi  same techniques work with inboxer etc. im guessing as timone said its  do with  python libraries. paul  comment by tim peters timone date 20040709 1035 message logged in yes userid31435 youll really have  ask about nx gimmicks   athlon list. spambayes is written entirely   python programming language  that never ever tries  execute code from  data region im very familiar with pythons implementation my only guess is that outlook itself  mapi try  do this when interfacing with extensions. or mark hammond is playing subject: re: [sm-users] autorespond plugin
emailtext: paul lesniewski wrote   on 2/8/08 kenmiles wrote   i am using squirrelmail 1.4.13 with dovecote  postfix  ubuntu 6.10.  is there  way  have  autorespond plugin send  vacation message  every  time  email is received from  same email address instead  just   first time  message is sent.   thats not  question   plugin. the plugin merely sets   responder /off  with  message. your mail delivery system does   actual autoresponding. you need  know how  configure your  autoresponse system. if you dont know how  do that read up   your mail system  ask   right forum. also note that local  user autoresponder  mail forwarder will also work  you    answer  your question will still be  same.    i dont think that is right. when looking at  plugin config file i found this line autorespondoptsvacationalias   s  changed it  autorespondoptsvacationalias  r 1  s which calls  vacation program  makes it send  response every day i think. regards kenneth.  view this message  context http//www.nabble.com/autorespondplugintp15361461p15372144.html sent from  squirrelmailusers mailing list archive at nabble.com.

subject: re: [bulk] [opensuse] a quick start - virtualbox howto
emailtext: alexey eremenko pecked at  keyboard  wrote  as regards  network cards sound cards  other such equipment is  it possible  have direct access  vbox  does this cause problems  with  host system?   no.   the problem is that if you enable such access your vm virtual  machine will no longer be isolated so  code will leak  it may  destroy data  your host physical pc.  this is very unsafe.  i would be very interested  where you got this info from. or perhaps you are talking about  windows guest   windows host machine.  ken schneider suse since version 5.2 june 1998

subject: [bug 5817]  new: poorly faked mta received headers
emailtext: http//issues.apache.org/spamassassin/showbug.cgi?id5817 summary poorly faked mta received headers product spamassassin version 3.2.4 platform other os/version other status new severity normal priority p5 component rules assignedto xrhspamassassin.apache.org reportedby qmitxmehrudersport.de i recently noticed quite  few spams with  poorly faked mta received header. the from ips   first  second received header are identical   second received is by  mx. i guess this is  sneak around mtatomx style rules. i havent checked  lot  spam  this yet though. also im not sure where  best add such  rule. maybe ill have  look next week when i get some time. each  any comment  hint welcome.  and now  two examples i found  my 10 scoring spam today from foobar sun feb 24 102738 2008 received from dsl.static812142840.ttnet.net.tr dsl.static812142840.ttnet.net.tr 81.214.28.40 may be forged by ... received from 81.214.28.40 by kilowog.blockstackers.com ... from foobar sun feb 24 102738 2008 received from 91.pool8549188.dynamic.orange.es 91.pool8549188.dynamic.orange.es 85.49.188.91 by ... received from 85.49.188.91 by mx2.free.fr ... btw all three spamples i had  look at today are downloadable software spams   mua claims  be the bat yeah again. however this time they did not screw up  date header.   you are receiving this mail because  you are  assignee   bug  are watching  assignee.

subject: [opensuse] 11.0 a2
emailtext: first impressions. fresh install  real machine went smoothly  one machine  trying  upgrade  11.0a1 virtualbox install failed  upgrade even one package. no errors occurred it just seemed  skip  part where software would be selected. since kde 4 is  default kde version installed  it is still fairly new there are numerous bugs that i hope are worked out before  gm release. but then that is why i am testing  spare hardware  help find  bugs. it also appears that  kde devs are taking lessons from  gnome devs where less control is better. the number  options available  config   control panel is far less then what i would expect based  past experience. this could be setup as  choice beginner  fewer options presented advanced  more config options presented. on freshly installed machine my logitech wheel mouse is not recognized. even after adding  appropriate info  xorg.conf. resizing any window larger   kde desktop requires  click   missing portion  make it visible. launching kde apps from  menu  via altf2 popup causes  sigsegv error  pop up  they run from  command line. more info  bug reports opened as i continue  test. bottom line keep up  great work as i think this will end up as  very good version not great because   kde4 bugs that will persist. but that is  be expected when you have  major ui change.  ken schneider suse since version 5.2 june 1998

subject: [uai] cfp: flairs-05 - evaluation and refinement of intelligent systems
emailtext: apologies if you receive this message more than once  please note that deadline  paper submission is october 22nd 2004  special track  evaluation  refinement  intelligent systems at 18th international florida artificial intelligence research society conference 2005 may 1618 2005 the adams mark hotel clearwater beach florida usa  the florida ai research society was founded  1987  promote  advance artificial intelligence. membership is open  all florida residents  nonresidents that attend our yearly conference. from its inception one major goal   society has been  promote ai thorough  conference. these conferences have been held yearly since  spring  1988. in 1995  conference title was changed  the international flairs conference  recognize  contribution   international participants within  conference. the 18th international flairs conference flairs2005 is held  may 1618 2005  clearwater beach fl usa. invited speakers  flairs2005 are lawrence hunter univ.  colorado martha pollack univ.  michigan ted senator darpa and david stork ricoh  stanford univ.. verification  validation  ai systems was  popular topic   last years flairs. more  more authors have realized that  lack  systematic methods  formal techniques  verification  validation v&v is often one important reason  not using ai systems  practice. the first contributions  this field were limited  classical ai systems. actually more  more papers  verification  validation  nonclassical kinds  systems like casebased systems e.g. knowledge processing principles learning principles e.g.  intelligent behavior are been published. moreover there is  community  system developers  users who express  strong need  validation techniques  their systems   ecommerce  elearning fielde.g.. thus we generalized  track titled as described here. the objective   special track is  focus   contributions  these fields   provide  environment  communicating different paradigms  approaches thus hopefully stimulating future cooperation  synergistic activities. the track will host any contributions  evaluate intelligent systems. verification  validation v&v are  most popular ones  any other kind  evaluation types are also welcome. this also includes  is not limited   evaluation issues  system development  evaluation  system certification including any contributions besides technical ones  this field   using evaluation results  knowledge maintenance  refinement. possible fields  related papers are  detecting  handling inconsistencies  other anomalies within knowledge bases  fundamentals  formal methods  verification  ai systems  fundamentals  formal methods  techniques  validity assessment  ai systems ai principles  intelligent behavior  general  special approaches  verify / validate certain kinds  ai systems rulebased casebased ...  special approaches  tools  evaluate systems   particular application field  knowledge base refinement  revision by using  results  evaluation  problems  system certification any paper related  these  similar areas are welcome flairs05 is  cooperation with the american association  artificial intelligence aaai. papers will be refereed  all accepted papers will appear   conference proceedings which will be published by aaai press. selected authors will be invited  submit extended versions  their papers   special issue   international journal  artificial intelligence tools iaait  be published  2006. call  papers a full paper up  singlespaced 6 pages paper should be submitted. please check  website www.flairs.com/flairs2005  information regarding submission. deadlines  paper submissions full paper due october 22 2004  notification letters sent  january 7 2005  camera ready copy due february 4 2005 program committee & referees  rainer knauf program cochair technical university  ilmenau germany  avelino gonzalez program cochair university  central florida fl usa  joachim baumeister wuerzburg university germany  scott y. harmon ph.d. zetetix oak park ca usa  stephane loiseau universite dangers france  mieczyslaw lech owoc wroclaw university  economics poland  silvie spreeuwenberg librt b.v. amsterdam the netherlands  takao terano graduate school  systems management university  tsukuba tokyo  setsuo tsuruta tokyo denki university tokyo japan  neli p. zlatareva central connecticut state university ct usa further information for further information contact rainer knauf jbbpyk.wydgotuilmenau.de  dr. joachim baumeister mailtoocdenuwhioaiwuerzburg.de applied informatics  artificial intelligence subject: re: [opensuse] how can i write man pages? linuxdoc/docbook anyone? report on manedit
emailtext: carlos e. r. schreef  i havent finished yet  i found  blocker.   the program does it job fairly well   locale encoding turns out   be  problem.   i asked  people   project  whom im translating their pages  whether they wanted  pages  latin1  utf8   answer is  neither    characters outside  ascii printable range must be encoded see   groffchar7  note that we use e rather than e.    this is  problem too with manual pages   suse distro they either  display well  latin 1   utf 8  not both. and using   encoding described  groffchar7 they display correctly  both. the  blocker is that manedit does not support that encoding.   i would have  write ole instead  ol which may be just   nuisance   coder  it is  big inconvenience   writer i can  not spell check  file  my sight doesnt see ol  gibberish  so i cant proofread  text.   /  but wait youre almost there the only thing you need is  sed script  convert  utf8 symbols  groffchar7 gibberish right? something like utf2groff /bin/sed f   convert utf 8  groffchar7 s//e/g s//e/g

subject: re: [opensuse]  unstable system - who is the culprit?
emailtext: on thu 20080207 at 1013 0100 per jessen wrote  randall r schulz wrote    offhand i dont know how  efficiency  todays power supplies   varies with  percentage  their rated output theyre producing. in   other words does  highercapacity psu consume more mains power     given level  consumption  its output side? if so you wouldnt   want  have such  large psu since that would be wasteful.   i havent looked at switchmode technology  quite some time  i  would expect  fairly fixed efficiency   8090 range quite  probably more. there will be  minimum consumption required  order   achieve optimal operation  otherwise i think  output power  will be e.g. 80   input power   rest is turned into heat.   say it another way...at 80 efficiency  150 watt supply   500 watt supply should either one pull  same current from  mains if they alternately supply  same 80 watt load ie mb...approximately 100 watts from  mains  each example. it would not be wasteful   environment... maybe  your wallet. tom  nm

subject: re: [opensuse]  unstable system - who is the culprit?
emailtext: tom patton wrote  on thu 20080207 at 1013 0100 per jessen wrote   randall r schulz wrote    offhand i dont know how  efficiency  todays power supplies  varies with  percentage  their rated output theyre producing. in  other words does  highercapacity psu consume more mains power    given level  consumption  its output side? if so you wouldnt  want  have such  large psu since that would be wasteful.   i havent looked at switchmode technology  quite some time  i  would expect  fairly fixed efficiency   8090 range quite  probably more. there will be  minimum consumption required  order   achieve optimal operation  otherwise i think  output power  will be e.g. 80   input power   rest is turned into heat.     say it another way...at 80 efficiency  150 watt supply    500 watt supply should either one pull  same current from  mains  if they alternately supply  same 80 watt load ie mb...approximately  100 watts from  mains  each example. it would not be wasteful    environment... maybe  your wallet.   tom  nm    youre forgetting there may be some additional power consumed by  power supply itself. this might be  bit more   larger supply. even with no load all power supplies draw some power.  use openoffice.org

emailtext: james knott wrote  tom patton wrote  on thu 20080207 at 1013 0100 per jessen wrote  randall r schulz wrote  offhand i dont know how  efficiency  todays power supplies  varies with  percentage  their rated output theyre producing. in  other words does  highercapacity psu consume more mains power    given level  consumption  its output side? if so you wouldnt  want  have such  large psu since that would be wasteful.  i havent looked at switchmode technology  quite some time  i  would expect  fairly fixed efficiency   8090 range quite  probably more. there will be  minimum consumption required  order   achieve optimal operation  otherwise i think  output power  will be e.g. 80   input power   rest is turned into heat.    say it another way...at 80 efficiency  150 watt supply    500 watt supply should either one pull  same current from  mains  if they alternately supply  same 80 watt load ie mb...approximately  100 watts from  mains  each example. it would not be wasteful    environment... maybe  your wallet.  youre forgetting there may be some additional power consumed by   power supply itself. this might be  bit more   larger supply.  even with no load all power supplies draw some power. but many power supplies are only efficient when they dont operate close  full load. kind regards philippe

emailtext: on saturday 09 february 2008 1008 philippe landau wrote  ...   but many power supplies are only efficient when  they dont operate close  full load. this seemed counterintuitive  me so i decided  do  little looking around. according   graph  page 14  power supplies a hidden opportunity  energy savings this is not  case. switching powersupplies have  efficiency peak when producing about 50  their maximum rated output. however  curve   low side   efficiency peak is much steeper than that   high side. so my suspicion was mostly correct. a psu that has more than twice  capacity that it will be called   supply will waste significantly more power than one being used   50  100 range.  kind regards philippe randall schulz

subject: re: [opensuse] opensuse 10.3 hangs after kernel update
emailtext: thanks jan  all your god suggestions while i did not have  live dvd  10.3  hand i did have  regular install dvd. since i had  spare partition  my harddisk i just installed  new fresh 10.3  that then mounted my original root partition  copied  kernel files there  update grubs menu.lst. the machine booted fine  i did  kernel update   fixed kernel  things are back  normal again. one thing i have noticed is any time i install  release  opensuse alongside another one so that i have multiple versions installed grub is installed again  i have all these grubs pointing  other installations  other grubs   various partitions. i can clean it all up after  installations so there is only one grub  i was wondering if there was  easy way  have just one master grub updated no matter how many other verions one installed  their machine? vahe  original message  from jan ritzerfeld to wkilxlocopensuse.org sent saturday february 9 2008 10505 am subject re opensuse opensuse 10.3 hangs after kernel update am freitag 8. februar 2008 schrieb carlos e. r.  the thursday 20080207 at 0932 0800 vahe avedissian wrote   i booted from  64b installation dvd  chose boot installed system    that only tried  boot  bad kernel i.e. system hangs with   same errors.   no you need  start  live system   rescue dvd mount your root  filesystem  chown  it. too bad i hoped that there is still  possibility  boot  installed system with  original kernel.  as somebody else wrote anders johansson  mount bind i know that was  reason  let vahe first try it  easy way. btw there is  bug report about  missing documentation   rescue process when using  dynamic /dev https//bugzilla.novell.com/showbug.cgi?id293691 gru jan  dont force it get  larger hammer.  to unsubscribe email opensuseunsubscripjopensuse.org for additional commands email opensusehelbopensuse.org  looking  last minute shopping deals? find them fast with yahoo search. http//tools.search.yahoo.com/newsearch/category.php?categoryshopping

emailtext: i would like  be able  send  receive faxes using my opensuse v10.3 system. a bit  looking around showed that there are not many applications  do this  actually only one hylafax which i thought likely  be more capable than  combination  sendfaxmgetty i have downloaded  installed hylafax. surprisingly hylafax does not sport  gui as far as i have been able  discover. i find it difficult  believe that many people having acquired  sophisticated operating system like suse will be content with commandline operation so i have  wonder if i have overlooked another available application. what do people do  fax service  suse? or do only few people use this os  faxing? i have stumbled upon  java app that is intended  be  gui  hylafax. this is susefax which seems  be  product  someone at suse  germany. it was first released  1997 sic  is also available   later beta v1.0beta3 dated 1999 even  x8664 at rpm.pbone.net. it is labeled src.rpm  suse v9. before i get into compiling it something i have not done so far i would like  ask some questions about it. the 1997 webpage says that  docs are  german only. a later user wrote   forum that  1999 release has english docs  all  labels   gui are  german  decade after first release  still  beta. does anyone have later information? has  developer recovered  desire  finish what he started? the program shouts halfdone abandonware fax apps  other oses make  sending operation  matter  printing from  application that created  document   fax app does susefax do that? this is not mentioned  any   webpages i have found. it is said only that one can send faxes from  phone book. so at minimum there are at least two stages  sending  fax. the hylafax webpage speaks   need  ghostscript. what is this ? since faxes arrive  raster form not as either ascii codes  postscript formatting information what does ghostscript have  contribute   fax function?  stan goodman qiryat tivon israel

subject: [opensuse] kde4 repository change (was: [opensuse-kde] kde:kde4 deleted
emailtext: bob s wrote  on friday 08 february 2008 040356 am stephan binner wrote   old kdekde4 repository is now deleted   new structure see  http//lists.opensuse.org/opensusekde/200801/msg00079.html  uummmmm.....ok. structure looks good. must be just dumb me. how do we go about  adding them? not so nice  way this was handled. just giving us  famous repodata/repomd.xml not found errors. so now server name stays software.opensuse.org  directory is /repositories/kde/kde4/stable/desktop/opensuse10.3/ /repositories/kde/kde4/stable/community/opensuse10.3/ /repositories/kde/kde4/stable/extraapps/opensuse10.3/ kde 4.0.1 is still  some ways alpha/beta software though as central pieces   user interface are still missing  have  be configured before they can be used by simple users. kind regards philippe  http//lists.opensuse.org/opensusekde/200801/msg00079.html opensusekde new repository layout  from dirk mueller  date thu 31 jan 2008 174345 0100  messageid 016344121298.26800.jcfaszqjxxxxxxx hi given that we have finally decided   new repository layout this is how it looks like kdekde4stabledesktop  only  bare desktop. it is also  repository  build against  your home project if you want  build your own apps. so it replaces  platform repository. kdekde4stableextraapps  addons that are released independently from kde amarok koffice etc  maintained by novell employees via e.g. opensuse factory kdekde4stablecommunity  anything else  same layout exists  unstable e.g. kde 4.1 snapshots kdekde4unstabledesktop kdekde4unstableextraapps kdekde4unstablecommunity  3 repositories are also duplicated as backports which will contain some   applications if they compile against  distro version  qt kdelibs  kdebaseruntime. this way you dont have  update your whole kde just  get  new e.g. amarok  digikam. kdekde4backportsdesktop kdekde4backportsextraapps kdekde4backportscommunity the other previously existing kde4 related repositories under kde prefix have already vanished  will disappear   near future. greetings dirk

subject: [uai] phd and postdoc postion at snn nijmegen
emailtext: phd student  postdoc position available at snn nijmegen. snn nijmegen is  research group dedicated  fundamental research   areas  machine learning  computational neuroscience. specific topics are bayesian networks approximate inference methods timeseries modeling bioinformatics expert systems stochastic control  collaborative decision making. the group consists currently  8 researchers  three programmers. in our group we have two positions available that can be filled at either  phd student level  at  postdoc level. see  job anouncements at http//www.mbfys.kun.nl/snn/nijmegen/index.php3?page29 the requirement   phd student position is  completed university degree  physics mathematics  computer science. the position is fulltime   period  4 years. the requirement   postdoc position is  phd  publications  one   above research topics. the postdoc position is fulltime   period  2.5 years. for more information see www.snn.kun.nl/nijmegen  contact dr. h.j. kappen jqmcsnn.kun.nl 31024 3614241  dr. w. wiegerinck kzsvsnn.kun.nl. applications should contain  complete cv  brief description  his  her research interests   copy   recent publication  dissertation optional. send your application before october 1 2004 either by email  dr. h.j. kappen jqmcsnn.kun.nl  dr. w. wiegerinck kzsvsnn.kun.nl  by ordinary mail  snn radboud university nijmegen geert grooteplein 21 6525 ez nijmegen  netherlands.

subject: re: [opensuse] intel 3945 wireless problem opensuse 10.3 - resolved!
emailtext: joe sloan wrote  chuck stuettgen wrote   the fix is   yast select configure   wireless card. select   hardware tab then change  kernel module   module name drop down  list from  ipw3945   iwl3945. save  settings  exit out   yast. reboot  laptop.   if  iwl3945 kernel module is not   list install it first then  reboot  change.    ack that is  good fix  except   reboots absolutely no need   any  that just rmmod  ipw3945  youre good  go. heres something i just found  points  where  real problem with hidden sites is when  awhile i assumed it was knetworkmanager....so did others. for almost 2 weeks ive been using  ipw3945 driver   standard ifup method  connect. i just changed from that driver   iwl3945 driver stopped  ipw driver  used yast  setup using  iwl driver with knetworkmanager.....just  see what happend. ive not been able  see hidden sites including my own at home with knetworkmanager.......now i can. so it would appear that this problem that plagues some others with different chipsets have  problem with  driver not knetworkmanager. thanks  chuck stuettgen  pointing this out fred  a because it messes up  order  which people normally read text. q why is topposting such  bad thing?

subject: re: branching
emailtext: on tue 20080805 at 1320 0400 will coleda wrote  on tue aug 5 2008 at 110 pm chromatic wrote   gah no maintenance releases please see mommy why did it take over five   years  release  new stable version  perl 5 with  bugfix i made    2002?   perhaps i used  official term when i didnt mean  here.   lets simplify i can easily see us needing at least dev   production branches one  which can be trunk which is one more  than we have now. we will definitely need multiple longlived branches. just  make explicit  reasoning data loss security  otherwise critical bugfixes that should be backported  one  more already released versions  rereleased immediately. thats  lot harder if you dont have release branches. of course you can branch lazily since releases are tagged. but we have  assume that there will be multiple longlived branches that wont merge  go away. however im against  practice  branching before release  stabilize  assumedcrazy trunk. i prefer  general way we do things now releases are made from  trunk code which is kept as highquality as possible small changes are made directly  trunk large changes are made   branch  merged  trunk when ready. the details may be ripe  improvement however. there seems  be  implicit assumption from at least some  us that  merge back  trunk should be  even needs  be  all  nothing affair. several scms make it easier  cherrypick changes from  branch merge them back  trunk  keep  diff  even  longlived feature development branch as small as possible. git  example combined with stacked git   similar tool has decent support  altering existing commits   branch  make them easier  merge piecemeal. i dont have enough svk fu  know how well this development model is supported there. f

subject: [spambayes-dev] spambayes core_server.py and related bits merged to	cvs head
emailtext: i just merged  code   new application coreserver.py   spambayes cvs head. when i checked   changes  head i got  bunch  messages like this cvs diff tag 1.1 refers   dead removed revision  file coreserver.py. cvs diff no comparison available. pass n  cvs diff? it looks like  checkin actually worked  ive never seen that message before. this new application scripts/coreserver.py is fundamentally  same as  preexisting pop3 proxy  uses  simple plugin scheme  support different protocol adapters. the only plugin written so far is spambayes/ xmlrpcplugin.py which as you might guess allows messages  be scored using xmlrpc calls. there are two methods score  scoremime. the latter is pretty much what we are used   essentially shoot  email  emaillike message over  pipe  get  score back. the former method maybe it should be named scoreform accepts  dictionary representing  form submission  set  extra tokens generated by  client such as was  submission from  anonymous user?   set  attachments. the last two args can be empty though because  xmlrpc constraints they cant be optional. the first application  this is likely    new roundupbased python tracker. i wrote  simple roundup auditor  that purpose today. ill be testing that over  next few days. the second application will likely be moinmoin. marian neagul is doing  google summer  code project  page classification which this might fit into nicely. in theory  web site can use it though as long as it can speak xmlrpc. btw before i merged i created  tag beforecoresvrmerge. i also created  aftercoresvrmerge tag after  big checkin. can people give  existing applications  whirl  make sure i didnt break anything? for reimar  marian  moinmoin gurus i did  very little bit  performance testing. roundtrip performance  my laptop mac powerbook g4  800mhz with both  server  client running   same machine ranged anywhere from 1050 bytes/ms. when i added  large payload  mime encoded jpeg file  9.5mb performance  terms  bytes/ms shot way up  as you would imagine overall time did as well. here are some figures attachment time bytes/ms size 9587824 30.7 sec 312 975978 3.7 sec 259 114794 0.5 sec 252 28675 0.2 sec 142 thx skip  spambayesdev mailing list bsfegmjrrhnqpython.org http//mail.python.org/mailman/listinfo/spambayesdev

subject: re: [opensuse] opensuse and faxes
emailtext: on 02/10/2008 0348 am stan goodman wrote  i would like  be able  send  receive faxes using my opensuse v10.3  system. a bit  looking around showed that there are not many  applications  do this  actually only one hylafax which i thought  likely  be more capable than  combination  sendfaxmgetty i have  downloaded  installed hylafax.  depending  your hardware there is at least one more. if you have  hp officejet that has fax capability there is hplip which provides  scanning printing  faxing. it sets up  printing queue   fax so as you mention further down you print from  app   fax printer  then use hplips gui hptoolbox  send  document. it works pretty well. i use it with  officejet 5610. hth  joe morris registered linux user 231871 running opensuse 10.3 x8664

computer science statistics  related areas. since its inception  1985  primary goal  this workshop has been  broaden research  both  these fields by promoting  exchange  ideas between them. we subject: [uai] cfp: challenges to decision support in a changing world (aaai sss)
emailtext: aaai 2005 spring symposium series call  participation march 2123 2005 stanford university california usa challenges to decision support in a changing world submission deadline october 8 2004 one   most daunting challenges faced by decision support systems is  perpetual change  their environment. existing decision support methodologies tools  frameworks are often difficult  scale up  adapt  changing knowledge workflow  operational setting. successful decision support systems need  fulfill  following three requirements  their design  implementation first  representation  reasoning techniques need  incrementally incorporate new subject matter knowledge along with new methods  information integration organization monitoring  analysis. second  systems need  adjust  changing policies regulations standards evolving operating procedures different decision makers  target groups  diverse operational settings. third  systems need  effectively operate   distributed infrastructure built  heterogeneous  evolving computing  networking platforms. adaptive systems that have  cope with change need  include methodologies that go outside single theories. for example systems that are based  probabilistic  decisiontheoretic principles will be typically unable  cope with change by themselves as neither probability theory nor decision theory say much about how decision models are constructed let alone how they should be modified. the general ai concepts  perception learning control abstraction  personalization must be inherently designed into  methodological architectural  operational aspects  adaptive systems from application design through software  hardware infrastructure support. this symposium aims at bringing together researchers with experience  interest  building adaptive decision support systems. since some domains such as biomedicine deal with numerous modes  reasoning this symposium aims at providing  coherent forum that will highlight various issues involved  will facilitate crossdisciplinary diffusion  methods  reasoning about  adapting  change. the central themes   symposium are 1 practical fielding  adaptive decision support systems  2 crucial technologies  successful adaptive decision support systems. we encourage submissions that address  are not limited  relevant issues   domains  biomedicine finance  business  military/government/homeland security. in particular we welcome submissions that address  challenges faced   solutions involved what worked what did not  why. we also welcome contributions that chart out new research agendas  identify specific cruc ial i ssues. submission information the symposium will consist  formal paper presentations as well as interdisciplinary panel  discussion sessions. potential participants are invited  submit either  6page full paper 5000 words maximum   12 page extended abstract 1500 words maximum outlining their relevant research activities  how they see their contribution   symposium. please submit papers  pdf format   cochairs marek druzdzel qttsjsis.pitt.edu  tzeyun leong zauihmvcomp.nus.edu.sg. please direct all correspondences   cochairs as well. organizing committee david aha naval research laboratory sraaic.nrl.navy.mil riccardo belazzi universita degli studi di pavia yzdnbyoi.lwxanaxbunipv.itt f. javier diez uned bgvpkidia.uned.es marek j.
