subject: a crime conundrum
emailtext: quite bizarre. http//ask.metafilter.com/72827/stolencarreturnedwithinminuteswhy can you help solve  somewhat bizarre  mysterious crime? heres  background story my friend owns  latemodel minivan  very good condition. she had  van parked   basement 3rd level b3   parking garage under  tokyo dome hotel which is adjacent   tokyo dome  sports arena  downtown tokyo seats 55000 people as well as  amusement park   small shopping mall. heres  link   map showing  position   hotel  dome  surroundings. the hotel was fully booked   japanese holiday period  only registered guests at  hotel would be able  gain access   hotel parking garage. my friend who lives  tokyo was able  park there that day however as she has  relative working at  hotel who gave her  pass. she  her family came   hotel  dinner arriving around 4pm. she returned   garage at around 9pm  same evening. she went  retrieve her car  couldnt find it   b3 level where shed parked. wondering if shed confused her parking place she went one level up  b2. there she found her van. aside from  fact that it was   wrong floor she noticed that it had been parked frontend  whereas she had backed her van into her parking place   b3 level. the car was locked nothing seemed remiss there were no traces that it had been broken into  nothing   car baby seat miscellaneous kids toys etc. was missing. my friend went first  hotel personnel who called  police. police arrived at  hotel  inspected  car. they dusted  fingerprints they took her fingerprint samples  compare. they questioned her about all details speaking with her from around 10pm til around 1am. they told her they had dusted  fingerprints   steering wheel  gear shift  had found nothing. the surveillance tapes which police showed  my friend show  man driving out   garage  her minivan at 630pm . tapes also show  man who is dressed identically  who appears  be  different person this also according  police who viewed  tapes returning only 12 minutes later at 642pm. the tapes show  man driving with  palms  his hands / his forearms so as not  leave prints. and although  weather was very hot that day  man men were wearing  unbuttoned dress shirt over  tshirt plus  baseball cap. police told my friend that  shirt tail wouldve been used  work  gearshift so as not  leave prints. this man had  kind  pass that  hotel guest would have  order  leave  garage   vehicle  return   vehicle. this pass is also necessary  gain entrance into  hotel building from  garage. this man was also seen  surveillance tapes shot inside  hotel. the street layout   hotel/dome complex requires  driver  take  rather roundabout route circling  dome  order  get out   complex  onto any other city streets. this route takes approximately 10 minutes. the car was gone from out   garage  only 12 minutes so its safe  say it didnt go very far one last thing  tokyo cops who talked  my friend told her that these guys seemed very professionsl  then they told her that theyd probably never be caught why would someone steal  car out   garage keep it  such  short time then have it returned so quickly by another person  identical clothing? j.

emailtext: on sat 20080209 at 1252 0500 james knott wrote  tom patton wrote   on thu 20080207 at 1013 0100 per jessen wrote     randall r schulz wrote       offhand i dont know how  efficiency  todays power supplies   varies with  percentage  their rated output theyre producing. in   other words does  highercapacity psu consume more mains power     given level  consumption  its output side? if so you wouldnt   want  have such  large psu since that would be wasteful.     i havent looked at switchmode technology  quite some time  i   would expect  fairly fixed efficiency   8090 range quite   probably more. there will be  minimum consumption required  order    achieve optimal operation  otherwise i think  output power   will be e.g. 80   input power   rest is turned into heat.       say it another way...at 80 efficiency  150 watt supply     500 watt supply should either one pull  same current from  mains   if they alternately supply  same 80 watt load ie mb...approximately   100 watts from  mains  each example. it would not be wasteful     environment... maybe  your wallet.     tom  nm        youre forgetting there may be some additional power consumed by   power supply itself. this might be  bit more   larger supply.  even with no load all power supplies draw some power.  i was correcting  previous post that seemed  say  rest would be turned into heat. a 500w supply will not pull 500w if  load is only 100. without comparing efficiency curves  two specific supplies it is all speculative at best. both supplies at standby load would likely be   rather poor efficiency zone... would still be just  small percentage   small load... thus very close  one another. the previous post seemed also  say that  output current would be 80   input current... that is not  correct way  look at  subject... tom  nm

subject: spambayes 1.1a4
emailtext: spambayes 1.1a4  fourth alpha release is out. you can download it from sourceforge . this is currently  source only release. there is as yet no outlook installer. whats new  1.1a4?  version 1.1a4 introduces  new application coreserver.py. this application is tailored  provide spam filtering by nonmail applications such as trac roundup moinmoin  your favorite blogging server. the external interface is xmlrpc. it also implements  plugin architecture so new protocol adapters can be added easily. what is spambayes?  the spambayes project is working  developing  statistical commonly although  little inaccurately referred  as bayesian antispam filter initially based   work  paul graham. the major difference between this  other similar projects is  emphasis  testing newer approaches  scoring messages. while most antispam projects are still working with  original graham algorithm we found that  number  alternate methods yielded  more useful response. spambayes is not  single application. the core code is  message classifier however there are several applications available as part   spambayes project which use  classifier  specific contexts. for  most part  current crop  applications all operate   client side  things however  number  people have experimented with using spambayes  mail servers  classify incoming mail  multiple users. contact help & feedback  please take  new alpha release out   spin around  block. report any feedback  problems you have with  new functionality  spambayesdevpython.org. to get general help with spambayes send your questions  spambayespython.org.  skip montanaro  iybzpobox.com  http//www.webfast.com/skip/  http//mail.python.org/mailman/listinfo/pythonannouncelist support  python software foundation http//www.python.org/psf/donations.html

subject: [uai] cfp: aisb symposium on normative multiagent systems (normas05)
emailtext: normas2005 is  one day symposium part   2005 aisb convention. the general theme   convention is social intelligence  interaction  animals robots  agents. it is held from april 12  april 2005 at  university  hertfordshire de havilland campus hatfield england. aisb conventions are organized by  largest ai society   united kingdom ssaisb which stands  society   study  artificial intelligence   simulation  behaviour. norms are essential  artificial agents that are  display behaviour comparable  human intelligent behaviour  collaborate with humans because  use  norms is  key  human social intelligence. norms play  central role  many social phenomena such as coordination cooperation decisionmaking etc. there is  increasing interest   role  norms  societies both inside as outside  agent community. now  time is ripe   symposium focussing  this central sociological concept given that  field  multiagent research is moving more  more from  individual cognitive focussed agent models  models  socially situated agents. normas therefore focuses  normative multiagent systems. normative multiagent systems combine theories  frameworks  normative systems with multiagent systems. thus these systems provide  promising model  human  artificial agent coordination because they integrate norms  individual intelligence. they are  prime example   use  sociological theories  multiagent systems  therefore   relation between agent theory   social sciences e.g. sociology philosophy economics legal science etc. normas2005 as part  aisb2005 will provide  excellent opportunity  meet researchers studying norms  cognitive science social sciences agent theory computer science philosophy etc.  discuss  current state  identify potential future directions  research issues. topics of interest the topics  this symposium include  are not restricted   following issues .. multiagent  society level .. balancing dynamics  statics at  agent micro  agent society macro level b.. coordination based  normative multiagent systems c.. emergence  conventions norms roles  normative multiagent systems d.. combining conventions with regulative permissive constitutive  other types  norms e.. relation between normas  contracts security  electronic institutions b.. agent level .. alternatives   extensions   homo economicus  bdi logics b.. extending logical frameworks  encompass norms  agent decision making c.. how  implement theories  norms  artificial agents c.. applications  normas .. multiagent social simulation models containing norms b.. mixing artificial  human agents  hybrid social systems important dates 31 october 2004 submissions deadline 22 november 2004 notification  authors 17 december 2004 camera ready copies deadline 14 january 2005 early registration deadline 1215 april 2005 aisb2005 convention proceedings the papers accepted   symposium will be published   aisb proceedings. moreover  best papers will be published   special issue   renowned international journal. submission details the length  each paper including figures  references should not exceed 12 pages. all papers must be submitted  pdf  postscript format. a format description will be issued shortly. papers are  be send   following email address verhagendsv.su.se. programme committee guido boella  dipartimento di informatica universita di torino cochair cristiano castelfranchi  institute  cognitive sciences  technologies istc italy paul davidsson  bth sweden andr meyer  tno netherlands maria fasli  essex university uk leendert van der torre  cwi amsterdam &tu delft netherlands cochair harko verhagen  dsv kth/su sweden cochair symposium website http//normas.di.unito.it/zope/aisb05/ aisb convention website http//aisb2005.feis.herts.ac.uk/

subject: re: [opensuse] after sles10 sp1 update
emailtext: on saturday 09 february 2008 083223 pm chris arnold wrote  i know this might be  wrong place  ask this  i am hoping that  someone else is using sles10  did  update today.....  i have been updating php code all day today using gedit. this morning i  did  update from zmd  among other thing that were updated was  readline. when i was finished updating code i closed gedit....then  remembered i had  change something else before i called it quits. much   my surprise  file was all  black. along with other files  blank. the reason i think it had something  do with  update   gedit is b/c i tared  folder up  copied it  my windoze box   said files have all  code  them???? i also opened  files  vim   they exhibited  same as gedit some blank  some all  blank.  i also restarted  server same thing. anybody else seen this? not trying  be  hole  if youre using sles you should be using novell support. if youre not paying  support with sles then you would probably be better off using something different. this ml is specific  opensuse though having said that i must admit im not sure  what youre problem could be so i am intrigued. could be someone else will post  suggestion  really this isnt really  proper forum  support. cheers kv

emailtext: update  /cvsroot/spambayes/spambayes in directory sc8prcvs8.sourceforge.net/tmp/cvsserv7047 modified files readme.txt log message add some directions about starting  xmlrpc core server. index readme.txt  rcs file /cvsroot/spambayes/spambayes/readme.txtv retrieving revision 1.66 retrieving revision 1.67 diff c2 d r1.66 r1.67  readme.txt 12 apr 2004 015926 0000 1.66  readme.txt 27 jun 2007 015949 0000 1.67   179182   179253   xmlrpc server     the xmlrpc server new  1.1a4 web interface is almost identical    pop3 proxy user interface. instead  proxying pop3 communications though  it provides  xmlrpc server your typically nonmail applications can use   score content submissions.   to install  configure it   1. unpack  install  distribution   tar xvfz spambayes1.1a4.tar.gz  cd spambayes1.1a4  python setup.py install   2. devote  runtime directory  it   sbdir/usr/local/spambayes/coreserver   whatever...  mkdir p sbdir   3. create  ini file   cd sbdir  cat  bayescustomize.ini eof  globals  verbosefalse   headers  includeevidencetrue  includescoretrue   tokenizer  recordheaderabsencetrue  summarizeemailprefixestrue  summarizeemailsuffixestrue  minereceivedheaderstrue  xpickaparturlstrue  xfancyurlrecognitionfalse  xlookupiptrue  lookupipcachesbdir/dnscache.pck  maximagesize100000  crackimagecachesbdir/imagecache.pck   crackimagestrue  imagesizetrue  ocrenginegocr  classifier  usebigramsfalse   categorization  hamcutoff0.2  spamcutoff0.85   storage  persistentstoragefilesbdir/hammie.db  persistentusedatabasepickle  messageinfostoragefilesbdir/messageinfo.fs   htmlui  displayscoretrue  eof   4. finally start it   bayescustomizesbdir/bayescustomize.ini coreserver.py m xmlrpcplugin   note that it creates both  web server defaulting  localhost8880    xmlrpc server defaulting  localhost8001.   procmail filtering   spambayescheckins mailing list pnperxdpvsarswdlppython.org http//mail.python.org/mailman/listinfo/spambayescheckins

emailtext: on sunday 10 february 2008 035329 carlos e. r. wrote  the saturday 20080209 at 2148 0200 stan goodman wrote   i would like  be able  send  receive faxes using my opensuse   v10.3 system. a bit  looking around showed that there are not many   applications  do this  actually only one hylafax which i   thought likely  be more capable than  combination    sendfaxmgetty i have downloaded  installed hylafax.     surprisingly hylafax does not sport  gui as far as i have been   able  discover. i find it difficult  believe that many people   having acquired  sophisticated operating system like suse will be   content with commandline operation so i have  wonder if i have   overlooked another available application. what do people do  fax   service  suse? mailtoduodenalswitch40yahoogroups.comduodenalswitchyahoogroups.co m sent fri 8 feb 2008 658 pm subject re duodenalswitch pre op patient.... hi mark i tend  think  myself as one   lucky ones  terms  smell is very well controlled by daily acidophilus intake its not as bad as it was preop weight lossive lost 95  my excess body weight food tolerance untoasted bread pasta  rice dont seem  set well  my tummy other than that i can  do eat almost anything  everything with  exception  i never have carbonated beverages with my meals i can apparently eat just about anything i want  as long as i get enough protein fluids  my supplements every day nothing seems  slow my weight loss. keep  mind with all  these factors  place i am  exception   rule. ymmv. i started taking  acidophilus because ive always been very prone  yeast infections even before  ds. i didnt realize that they were helping with gas odor until i ran out  lived without them  about  week ive never let that happen again lol. i take them religiously twice  day. as far as recovery time some people seem  experience  turning  corner experience at 45 weeks postop  open surgery lap recovery time can be significantly less. it didnt work that way  me however. until about week 6 i pretty much felt like id been run over by  truck. then very gradually i began  feel more like myself. it was so gradual that i was probably at 10 weeks when i realized hey its been weeks since ive felt like crap lol. for about two months food did not taste good  me. no food tasted good. my surgeon assured me this would change  it has. i love food again. bread rice  noodles make me feel just sort  yucky  dont appeal  me much. if i eat simple carbs with no fat/protein like snow cones  cotton candy my tummy gets upset. everything else is  go. for  first few months maybe 6 months? i felt like i couldnt eat enough  one sitting. my meals were all onecourse affairs because by  time i was done  protein i needed i was too stuffed  eat any carbs now im very satisfied with  amount  food i can eat. i can probably eat about 8oz   sitting. if its  longer meal like  lunch date with  friend i can eat  lot more than that. i bet over  course  two  three hours i can polish off maybe 14oz  so  food. ive lost 145lbs. as ive said i realize my experience isnt typical. but i love my ds  would do it again   heart beat however if youre really concerned about  smell factor you may want  check into  vbg vertical banded gastroplasty which is just  stomach part   ds. in other words you get  restriction you cant eat very much at one time  none   malabsorption  bowel issues that come with  reworking   intestines. best  luck norine original message from hyperlink mailtoduodenalswitch40yahoogroups.comduodenalswitchyahoogroups.co m subject: [fork] personal data
emailtext: in  ongoing ebb  flow  privacy where do we stand now? open all over  cloaked with protection?  forwarded message  subject effector 20.38 newsweek exposes telcos secret lobbying campaign  myspace  facebook plan  use personal data  targeted advertising personal data is  hot commodity. all sorts  businesses trade  data concerning what we buy how much credit we have where we live what our interests are. this information is sold  advertisers who then eagerly use it  more precisely target people whom they hope will be interested  their products leading  all  those annoying catalogs that litter your doorstep  example   junk emails that choke your inbox every day. luckily   advertising industry modern web users have begun voluntarily providing all  their personal details  social networking sites like facebook  myspace. users  these sites happily upload all sorts  personal information about what books  music they like where they shop who their friends are  where they live. while users  these sites may imagine that they control  information  their profile pages advertisers are salivating at  thought  all that personal data just waiting  be processed analyzed  turned into profit. recently both facebook  myspace have announced plans  do just that. find out more  our post http//www.eff.org/deeplinks/archives/005454.php

subject: re: branching
emailtext: on tuesday 05 august 2008 123550 geoffrey broadwell wrote  we will definitely need multiple longlived branches. just  make  explicit  reasoning data loss security  otherwise critical  bugfixes that should be backported  one  more already released  versions  rereleased immediately. thats  lot harder if you dont  have release branches. of course you can branch lazily since releases  are tagged. but we have  assume that there will be multiple  longlived branches that wont merge  go away. thats horrible. i doubt you give morphine   five year old who falls  scrapes his knee. this is  equivalent  releasing software. i can see patching  previous release  case   critical bugfix  if we get   habit  encouraging users  expect updates  anything older than  previous stable release  free weve doomed  project. point releases every month. major releases every three months. complete  utter refusal  support users who expect that they can install parrot 1.0  get free support from  mailing list  irc   next eight  ten years. if we dont set those expectations now we might avoid  problem  these leeches   future. again see perl 5   example  why maintaining multiple stable branches doesnt work why encouraging people not  upgrade doesnt work why release candidates dont work  why featurebased releases dont work.  however im against  practice  branching before release   stabilize  assumedcrazy trunk. i prefer  general way we do  things now releases are made from  trunk code which is kept as  highquality as possible small changes are made directly  trunk  large changes are made   branch  merged  trunk when ready. agree.  the details may be ripe  improvement however. there seems  be   implicit assumption from at least some  us that  merge back   trunk should be  even needs  be  all  nothing affair. traditionally it has been. if mergebacks are small  frequent i can live with longlived branches. the problem isnt that branches live too long. the problem is that features are too big  take too long  develop. small working isolated steps are always better than big thuds. branches only seem  protect us from those big thuds by keeping trunk stable. if you cant keep your branch stable... well theres another problem obvious  anyone who watched  concurrency branch.  c
